history.content:
Honestly, none of those, except as you rightly said, possibly 188.

Note that simply having an edX course doesn't do much as we as Berkeley students, have access to all webcasts of previous semesters for most classes anyway, and additionally, we can get access to course assignments and notes easily (if the course has a public website). So, in principle, you can self-study almost every course, in terms of having access to materials but the question is, would you be able to, without the assistance of course staff..
